WEBVTT

00:01.958 --> 00:03.220
- [thunder crashing]

00:03.264 --> 00:09.009
- ["CreepShow" theme music
plays]

00:23.371 --> 00:30.204
♪

00:30.247 --> 00:36.166
- [ghostly choir]

00:42.781 --> 00:45.045
- [evil cackling]

00:45.088 --> 00:49.962
- ♪♪

00:53.879 --> 01:05.848
- ♪

01:21.081 --> 01:22.908
- EVAN MILLER: When are
we going to acknowledge

01:22.952 --> 01:25.868
that even with
medical insurance in America,

01:25.911 --> 01:29.001
it is impossible to afford
the lifesaving medication

01:29.045 --> 01:31.482
that this mother needs for
her daughter?

01:31.526 --> 01:34.964
She's sick, and she
will die without it.

01:35.007 --> 01:37.706
When is our government
gonna wake up

01:37.749 --> 01:39.838
and start taking care
of its own?

01:39.882 --> 01:43.103
Access to healthcare
is a human right.

01:43.146 --> 01:45.322
No citizen of our great country

01:45.366 --> 01:47.803
should be forced to cross
an international border

01:47.846 --> 01:50.501
just to buy the lifesaving
medication that they need.

01:50.545 --> 01:52.721
- WOMAN ON TV: My daughter
needs her medication to survive.

01:52.764 --> 01:54.157
We can't afford it here.

01:54.201 --> 01:55.463
- MAN ON TV:
I love this country,

01:55.506 --> 01:57.247
but we need to see some change.

01:59.467 --> 02:01.121
- I'm House Representative
Evan Miller,

02:01.164 --> 02:02.687
and I approve this message.

02:04.646 --> 02:15.004
- ♪

02:15.047 --> 02:16.484
- Ahh...
- [bus horn honks]

02:18.442 --> 02:20.096
- Jeez.

02:20.140 --> 02:30.802
- ♪

02:40.421 --> 02:41.770
- MAN: All right, come on!

02:41.813 --> 02:42.640
Let's get everything
set up out front.

02:42.684 --> 02:44.294
- MAN: Over here!

02:44.338 --> 02:46.818
- OFFICER: Well, shit.

02:46.862 --> 02:49.952
It's gonna be a whole
goddamn thing, isn't it?

02:49.995 --> 02:51.736
- MAN: Let's get
the banner centered.

02:51.780 --> 02:53.869
Come on, a little to the left.
Little to the left, people.

02:56.915 --> 02:58.526
And there we are.

03:03.052 --> 03:04.836
Okay, everyone!

03:04.880 --> 03:06.838
Let's form kind of a semicircle
around the front here.

03:06.882 --> 03:16.718
- ♪

03:16.761 --> 03:20.287
- [applause]

03:20.330 --> 03:22.114
- Mm, mm, mm.

03:22.158 --> 03:26.902
- [stomach gurgling]

03:26.945 --> 03:30.035
- Thank you.
It's very kind, thank you.

03:30.079 --> 03:31.950
- [stomach gurgling]

03:31.994 --> 03:36.346
- Now, folks, we all just shared
a long journey across the border

03:36.390 --> 03:39.567
to a Canadian pharmacy
to send a message back

03:39.610 --> 03:42.265
to real Americans like
yourselves

03:42.309 --> 03:46.878
about the need to reform
our broken healthcare system.

03:46.922 --> 03:49.707
The fact that you're all
standing here before me today--

03:49.751 --> 03:51.100
- [stomach gurgling]
- EVAN: --is a clear sign

03:51.143 --> 03:54.234
that our system
is corrupt and broken.

03:54.277 --> 03:55.931
- Mai.

03:55.974 --> 03:58.238
- EVAN: --and it's time for
our government to wake--

03:58.281 --> 04:00.892
- This might do the trick, okay?
It should settle your stomach.

04:00.936 --> 04:02.503
- EVAN: Now, my team's been
telling me that the video

04:02.546 --> 04:03.982
that we made--

04:04.026 --> 04:06.202
- That's better, isn't it?
- [coughs]

04:06.246 --> 04:08.291
- EVAN: --which means,
right now--

04:08.335 --> 04:11.163
- She's okay.
She just needs to eat.

04:11.207 --> 04:12.774
- EVAN: --about the
importance of access

04:12.817 --> 04:14.776
to low-cost prescription
medication.

04:14.819 --> 04:16.386
- [applause]

04:16.430 --> 04:17.866
- Yeah, let's take that
enthusiasm all the way

04:17.909 --> 04:19.302
to Washington!

04:19.346 --> 04:24.046
- [applause]

04:30.139 --> 04:32.576
- [exhales]

04:34.056 --> 04:35.579
Another 10 minutes,

04:35.623 --> 04:37.625
I would've been loading
the boxes into my truck.

04:37.668 --> 04:40.018
- Well, looks like
we got lucky, then.

04:40.062 --> 04:42.673
Thank you for
accommodating us, Officer.

04:42.717 --> 04:44.806
All right, everybody,
come on in.

04:44.849 --> 04:48.766
- [indistinct chatter]

04:48.810 --> 04:50.159
- How are you doing, there?
We're almost home.

04:50.202 --> 04:51.856
We're almost home.

04:53.728 --> 04:55.817
Good to be back, huh?
[laughs] Almost.

04:59.603 --> 05:04.347
- Excuse me, uh, your
girl okay there, ma'am?

05:04.391 --> 05:06.567
- You know, Officer, many of
these fine folks here have

05:06.610 --> 05:09.352
some very serious medical
issues,

05:09.396 --> 05:10.701
our country's failed them.

05:10.745 --> 05:12.660
- Mm.
- Hence the reason for our trip.

05:14.401 --> 05:17.229
- Okay, now folks, this
whole system's automated now.

05:17.273 --> 05:19.971
All you gotta do is
step up to the line,

05:20.015 --> 05:22.800
put your picture page of
your passport into the scanner.

05:22.844 --> 05:26.064
You look up, and
it'll take your picture.

05:26.108 --> 05:29.372
It'll go green, and
it'll let you on through.

05:29.416 --> 05:31.766
- [stomach gurgling]

05:31.809 --> 05:35.813
- So, friend.

05:35.857 --> 05:37.728
You know, this is
actually my home district.

05:37.772 --> 05:40.209
It'd be fine thing to
count on your support.

05:40.252 --> 05:43.125
- Well, Congressman, we
probably don't see eye to eye,

05:43.168 --> 05:45.693
you know what I mean?

05:45.736 --> 05:47.869
- What's your number-one issue?

05:47.912 --> 05:49.349
Sovereign citizen?

05:49.392 --> 05:51.046
- [stomach gurgling]
- EVAN: Guns rights?

05:51.089 --> 05:53.265
You know, Karl Marx
once said that any attempt--

05:53.309 --> 05:55.311
- --to disarm the workers

05:55.355 --> 05:57.748
must be frustrated
by force if needed.

05:57.792 --> 06:00.316
Don't quote Marx to me, man.

06:00.360 --> 06:02.927
Don't suit your milquetoast
centrist policies.

06:02.971 --> 06:05.277
You ain't no real leftist.

06:05.321 --> 06:07.454
You know what I mean?

06:07.497 --> 06:11.545
- [laughs] Are you
some backwoods,

06:11.588 --> 06:13.895
manifesto-writing communist?

06:13.938 --> 06:15.810
- Born and bred red, baby.

06:15.853 --> 06:17.289
Why do you think
Border Patrol banished me

06:17.333 --> 06:18.987
out to the armpit of nowhere

06:19.030 --> 06:23.513
to watch technology steal
my job?

06:23.557 --> 06:27.387
- I--I--I can't tell if you're
kidding or not, there, Comrade.

06:27.430 --> 06:29.258
- I'll tell you what.

06:29.301 --> 06:30.868
You start talking
about guillotines

06:30.912 --> 06:33.393
and you got my vote, man, 100%.

06:33.436 --> 06:36.091
Simple as that.

06:36.134 --> 06:38.963
Now, you have a
good evening, sir.

06:39.007 --> 06:40.661
You gotta go on
through yourself.

06:40.704 --> 06:41.966
There you go.

06:44.491 --> 06:47.189
- [stomach gurgling]

06:47.232 --> 06:48.973
- 'Scuse me, ma'am.

06:50.758 --> 06:54.022
Would you step outta line
for a moment, please?

06:54.065 --> 06:57.373
- Um, is there
really a need for it?

06:57.417 --> 06:58.983
- Can you please
just step out of line

06:59.027 --> 07:02.770
and walk over to
that table, there?

07:02.813 --> 07:04.859
No, no, no, no, no, no.

07:04.902 --> 07:06.469
Take your pocketbook with you.

07:06.513 --> 07:08.079
Sort of the whole point.

07:11.518 --> 07:13.911
- Okay. I'll be right back,
sweetheart, okay?

07:13.955 --> 07:17.567
- OFFICER: Mm, mm, mm, mm.

07:17.611 --> 07:19.308
I saw that, Miss.

07:21.876 --> 07:23.617
Hand it over, see what you got.

07:28.665 --> 07:30.362
Do you know what's in this?

07:30.406 --> 07:31.886
- [indistinct chatter]
- [stomach gurgling]

07:31.929 --> 07:33.496
- [retches]
- [exclaiming]

07:35.324 --> 07:40.938
- Okay. It appears you've been
feeding her a lot of pills.

07:40.982 --> 07:42.940
- She's sick, but
she's not contagious.

07:42.984 --> 07:45.552
I mean, if we could just get--
- Okay, then.

07:45.595 --> 07:49.817
Why don't you, uh, head on
through the passport check

07:49.860 --> 07:52.515
and I'll talk to your mommy
a little bit, okay?

07:52.559 --> 07:54.517
- [indistinct chatter]

07:54.561 --> 07:56.214
- There you go.

07:59.348 --> 08:01.219
I need to look into
your purse there, please.

08:04.701 --> 08:06.486
Thank you.

08:08.400 --> 08:11.142
Anything sharp or dangerous?

08:11.186 --> 08:13.318
Uh, excuse me?

08:13.362 --> 08:17.801
- Sorry, what? Oh, no.

08:17.845 --> 08:19.716
- Mm-kay.

08:23.285 --> 08:25.287
Oh, shit.

08:25.330 --> 08:29.857
Pardon my language, ma'am,
but I'm sorry, this is not good.

08:29.900 --> 08:32.860
You can't carry this much
medication across the border,

08:32.903 --> 08:34.731
prescription or not.

08:34.775 --> 08:37.604
- Well, half of it
belongs to my daughter.

08:37.647 --> 08:42.043
- Okay. If that's
how you wanna play it.

08:44.698 --> 08:46.003
[clears throat]

08:48.919 --> 08:50.486
Here we go.

08:50.530 --> 08:54.795
Split like this,
you're both over the limit.

08:54.838 --> 08:58.102
Way over,
not to mention the fact

08:58.146 --> 09:02.019
some of these
are illegal in the States.

09:02.063 --> 09:03.543
- EVAN: Look at this, we've
got an Asian-American citizen

09:03.586 --> 09:05.980
being harassed by Border Patrol.
Now, if I intervene,

09:06.023 --> 09:08.069
we could go viral
twice in one day, you know?

09:08.112 --> 09:09.897
Show that I can step into power,

09:09.940 --> 09:11.942
but that I also care about
the marginalized communities.

09:11.986 --> 09:13.901
I mean, I don't know,
what do you think?

09:13.944 --> 09:15.467
- Yeah, sure.

09:15.511 --> 09:19.559
- Now, ladies and gentlemen,

09:19.602 --> 09:22.257
if y'all don't mind following me
to the waiting area,

09:22.300 --> 09:24.607
we'll all go in and take a seat
until we all sort this out.

09:24.651 --> 09:26.609
Ma'am, this way with you.

09:26.653 --> 09:28.393
- This is gonna be good.
Go, go, go...

09:28.437 --> 09:30.657
- OFFICER: Won't be long, then--
uh, then y'all be on your way.

09:30.700 --> 09:33.573
This way, please.
- [people complaining]

09:35.836 --> 09:38.403
That's it, this way.

09:38.447 --> 09:40.275
Here you go, right in here.

09:40.318 --> 09:41.798
There you go.

09:41.842 --> 09:43.844
- Okay, guys, let's do this.

09:47.238 --> 09:48.936
Uh, this is lovely.

09:48.979 --> 09:50.067
- OFFICER: This
won't be too long.

09:50.111 --> 09:51.634
I'll be right with you.

09:51.678 --> 09:52.983
That's it.

09:54.594 --> 09:55.943
Hey, go on in.

09:55.986 --> 09:58.510
No, no, no, no, Momma.
You stay with me.

09:58.554 --> 10:01.905
Just go sit down, honey.
Be right there.

10:01.949 --> 10:04.952
There you go.
We're gonna go this way.

10:04.995 --> 10:06.431
Here we go.

10:07.955 --> 10:10.000
- [heavy breathing]

10:10.044 --> 10:12.046
- [stomach gurgling]

10:17.660 --> 10:20.532
- [pants]

10:21.795 --> 10:25.494
[growls]

10:25.537 --> 10:30.412
- Hey, excuse me!
Excuse me! Thank you!

10:30.455 --> 10:32.588
Gotta go, right?

10:32.632 --> 10:35.112
You sure you're okay?

10:35.156 --> 10:37.419
Come on, l-l-let's
find you some water, okay?

10:37.462 --> 10:43.207
- ♪

10:43.251 --> 10:47.777
- [pants]

10:55.132 --> 10:58.570
- [stomach gurgling]

10:58.614 --> 11:06.666
- ♪

11:06.709 --> 11:09.277
- [banging]

11:09.320 --> 11:13.020
- [stomach gurgling]

11:15.718 --> 11:18.982
- [pants]

11:21.506 --> 11:25.554
- [heartbeat]

11:26.990 --> 11:31.821
- [stomach gurgling]

11:38.523 --> 11:41.744
- [grunts, groans]
- [heartbeat quickens]

11:41.788 --> 11:45.052
- [slimy, tearing sound]

11:45.095 --> 11:50.231
- ♪

11:56.063 --> 11:57.194
- Hey.
- [snaps]

11:57.238 --> 11:58.587
- Come with me.

11:59.631 --> 12:01.024
Come on, come on, come on.

12:05.376 --> 12:07.378
- [buzz]

12:07.422 --> 12:08.858
- There you go.

12:08.902 --> 12:10.773
- I really need to get
back to my daughter.

12:10.817 --> 12:15.212
- Mm-hmm. Well, the quicker
we get this done, the better.

12:15.256 --> 12:23.917
- ♪

12:32.055 --> 12:35.450
- [phone game beeping]

12:45.373 --> 12:47.505
- WOMAN'S VOICE:
[whispers] Jonah...

12:47.549 --> 12:59.517
- ♪

13:02.129 --> 13:03.434
- Passport, please.

13:06.481 --> 13:09.092
Okay. First thing's first.

13:09.136 --> 13:12.052
I'm sincerely sorry
that America has failed you,

13:12.095 --> 13:13.967
especially as a
lady and a minority.

13:14.010 --> 13:16.143
I cannot even imagine.

13:16.186 --> 13:18.841
But you know what?

13:18.885 --> 13:21.801
It's the whole goddamn
corrupt system, isn't it?

13:21.844 --> 13:23.585
Your girl, she needs her meds.

13:23.628 --> 13:25.369
And you'll do anything
to get 'em for her.

13:25.413 --> 13:28.982
I--I get that. I truly do.

13:29.025 --> 13:32.812
But making trips up to Canada is
not a viable long-term solution,

13:32.855 --> 13:34.901
you get me?

13:34.944 --> 13:38.295
You get home and back
a better candidate.

13:38.339 --> 13:40.080
- Sir, can I--

13:40.123 --> 13:43.083
- Please, allow me
to say my piece.

13:43.126 --> 13:44.780
Despite it being illegal to film

13:44.824 --> 13:47.652
at a border crossing like
this one,

13:47.696 --> 13:50.307
she's got a camera
rolling out there.

13:50.351 --> 13:54.224
And when that video gets out,
if I'm caught not doing my job,

13:54.268 --> 13:58.185
well, then we're
all screwed, aren't we?

13:58.228 --> 14:01.841
So, what we're gonna do is
you're going to just sit here

14:01.884 --> 14:04.278
for a minute. You're gonna nod.

14:04.321 --> 14:06.497
You're gonna take your
pills and be on your way.

14:06.541 --> 14:07.759
Is that okay with you?

14:07.803 --> 14:09.022
- No.
- OFFICER: No?

14:09.065 --> 14:10.762
- I need to leave now!

14:10.806 --> 14:12.939
My daughter just
threw up her medication.

14:12.982 --> 14:15.332
If she doesn't take
the pills, then, uh--

14:15.376 --> 14:16.943
- [rapid knocking]

14:16.986 --> 14:18.814
- Are you holding this
woman against her will?

14:18.858 --> 14:22.470
- See what I gotta
put up with? Hm?

14:22.513 --> 14:23.993
Be right back.

14:25.690 --> 14:28.389
- WOMAN'S VOICE:
[whispers] Jonah...

14:32.741 --> 14:36.353
Down here.

14:36.397 --> 14:47.538
- ♪

14:53.153 --> 14:56.765
- [pants]

14:56.808 --> 14:58.810
- [squishy noises]

14:58.854 --> 15:02.205
- [quickening heartbeat]

15:02.249 --> 15:13.129
- ♪

15:13.173 --> 15:14.696
- [hisses]
- JONAH: [gasps]

15:14.739 --> 15:17.873
- Okay, get this again.
- [buzz]

15:17.917 --> 15:20.745
- Congressman, do you mind?
I'm trying to do my job.

15:20.789 --> 15:22.138
- I do not mind at all, sir,

15:22.182 --> 15:25.272
except for the fact that
I will not stand idly by

15:25.315 --> 15:29.319
and watch an American citizen
be harassed by the fascist whim

15:29.363 --> 15:31.147
of some two-bit security guard

15:31.191 --> 15:33.062
drunk on whatever power
he's afforded.

15:35.195 --> 15:42.854
- ♪

15:44.247 --> 15:45.770
- [no audible speech]

15:50.210 --> 15:55.606
- ♪

15:55.650 --> 15:56.868
- Hm?

16:12.493 --> 16:13.755
- ♪

16:13.798 --> 16:14.886
- Aah!

16:14.930 --> 16:16.236
- OFFICER: All right, ma'am,

16:16.279 --> 16:17.759
I think you've filmed
quite enough.

16:17.802 --> 16:19.065
- EVAN: No, no, no.
You keep right on rolling.

16:19.108 --> 16:23.286
Sir, I demand that
you release this woman.

16:23.330 --> 16:25.332
- You demand?

16:25.375 --> 16:29.075
Well, if that's how you want to
expand your political capital,

16:29.118 --> 16:31.555
ma'am, you go ahead
and keep filming.

16:31.599 --> 16:33.383
- EVAN: That's right.

16:33.427 --> 16:35.951
- Now, I figure you got your
speech and you got a shot of

16:35.995 --> 16:38.084
a guy you can spin
any way you want.

16:38.127 --> 16:40.086
But then of course you got
your own flagrant display

16:40.129 --> 16:43.698
of abuse of power, don't you?
- Excuse me?

16:43.741 --> 16:46.962
- You never even asked why
I pulled this woman aside.

16:47.006 --> 16:48.224
- [gasps]

16:48.268 --> 16:52.924
- ♪

16:52.968 --> 16:55.014
- OFFICER: You had a
potential drug trafficker

16:55.057 --> 16:57.059
on your official campaign bus--
- EVAN: A drug trafficker?

16:57.103 --> 17:00.584
- OFFICER: --with a quantity of
drugs that far exceeds legal--

17:00.628 --> 17:02.064
- [screams] Hurry!
- [bangs on window]

17:02.108 --> 17:04.240
- Please open the door!
- Ma'am--

17:04.284 --> 17:06.155
- You really think
that this poor woman--

17:06.199 --> 17:08.114
- Calm down.
- --is dealing in black market--

17:08.157 --> 17:09.419
- Mai!

17:09.463 --> 17:11.465
- She's got about
two dozen boxes

17:11.508 --> 17:14.163
of illegal
prescription pills, there.

17:14.207 --> 17:16.644
Those can be some sort
of amphetamine cocktail.

17:16.687 --> 17:18.950
- Oh, unbelievable.
Are you kidding me?

17:18.994 --> 17:20.909
- Look, you saw her daughter.

17:20.952 --> 17:24.260
- ♪

17:24.304 --> 17:26.001
- You tell me she
didn't look like she was

17:26.045 --> 17:27.698
going through with--
- --drawls?

17:27.742 --> 17:29.352
- Ma'am, just a minute!
- I'll tell you what I saw--

17:29.396 --> 17:32.051
a terrible example of--
of racial profiling.

17:32.094 --> 17:33.313
- You saw nothing.
- [banging on window]

17:33.356 --> 17:35.097
- I saw nothing?
- Ma'am, please! Please!

17:35.141 --> 17:37.621
- I know what I saw, sir.
- Ma'am, Miss, please...

17:37.665 --> 17:40.363
- [sobs]

17:40.407 --> 17:43.018
- Sit down, sit down.
- EVAN: Calm down, calm down.

17:43.062 --> 17:44.498
We're gonna get to
the bottom of this.

17:44.541 --> 17:45.890
- OFFICER: This is for
your own good, ma'am.

17:45.934 --> 17:48.023
- No!
- That is not necessary.

17:48.067 --> 17:49.546
You know what?
It's gonna be okay.

17:49.590 --> 17:51.722
Tell him what's in these.

17:51.766 --> 17:55.422
- I don't know! I don't know.
- Well, what?

17:55.465 --> 17:57.685
Just read the back of the box.

17:57.728 --> 18:01.123
- I can't, okay?
I don't read Chinese.

18:01.167 --> 18:04.257
- You can't read?
- Chinese.

18:04.300 --> 18:07.086
- I'm not that kind of Asian!

18:07.129 --> 18:09.566
- Well, what the hell
kind of Asian are you?

18:09.610 --> 18:11.873
- Uh, and there it is!

18:11.916 --> 18:14.441
Miss, you get
that video back to town

18:14.484 --> 18:17.008
and you auction it off to
the highest bidder and get rich.

18:17.052 --> 18:18.358
- EVAN: Wait a second.

18:18.401 --> 18:19.663
You son of a bitch,
you set me up!

18:19.707 --> 18:22.884
- Huh? You can go, ma'am.

18:22.927 --> 18:26.235
Thank you for the extra
few minutes of your time.

18:26.279 --> 18:27.584
Mm.

18:27.628 --> 18:30.587
- [deep, heavy breathing]

18:30.631 --> 18:32.633
- Whoa!

18:32.676 --> 18:34.809
[grunts] Hey!

18:34.852 --> 18:37.507
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

18:37.551 --> 18:41.642
Hey! Hey, hey, hey.
Give me my firearm.

18:41.685 --> 18:44.645
- [screaming in background]
- Give me the key.

18:44.688 --> 18:47.169
- [screaming]

18:47.213 --> 18:48.779
- [hisses]

18:48.823 --> 18:51.130
- Don't be difficult.
You're safer in here.

18:51.173 --> 18:52.740
Now, hand over the gun.

18:52.783 --> 18:53.958
Miss.

18:54.002 --> 18:55.003
- [gunshot]
- [screams]

18:55.046 --> 18:56.309
- [glass shattering]

18:56.352 --> 18:57.571
- No! Damn, woman!
What the hell?

18:57.614 --> 18:59.355
- Mai!

18:59.399 --> 19:01.923
- [shrieks]

19:01.966 --> 19:03.316
- Mai!

19:03.359 --> 19:06.580
- Hey, hey! Miss!
Easy. I need my gun!

19:06.623 --> 19:09.931
- I told you that my
daughter needed me, okay?

19:09.974 --> 19:12.107
And now she's feeding!

19:12.151 --> 19:14.065
Goddamn it, she needs her
medication

19:14.109 --> 19:16.720
to keep her condition
under control!

19:16.764 --> 19:19.941
- OFFICER: [grunts]
- Let me go!

19:19.984 --> 19:21.943
- I'm sorry.
I can't do that.

19:21.986 --> 19:22.944
- No!

19:22.987 --> 19:25.294
[sobbing] No!

19:25.338 --> 19:28.906
[pants]

19:30.952 --> 19:33.302
- [grunts]

19:33.346 --> 19:34.695
- [glass shattering]

19:34.738 --> 19:36.740
- [grunts]

19:43.007 --> 19:47.751
[pants] Whoa.

19:56.412 --> 19:59.807
Sir?
- [stammers]

20:02.897 --> 20:06.248
- OFFICER: Oh my god.
What happened?

20:06.292 --> 20:07.728
Oh, they were butchered!

20:07.771 --> 20:12.472
Oh, Christ almighty.

20:12.515 --> 20:15.953
I'm sorry, sir.

20:15.997 --> 20:17.216
Come on.

20:17.259 --> 20:18.956
- No, no, no...

20:19.000 --> 20:20.654
- Come on, pull
yourself together, man!

20:20.697 --> 20:22.003
Buck up!

20:22.046 --> 20:23.961
- [pants]

20:24.005 --> 20:26.137
Okay. Okay.

20:26.181 --> 20:31.621
- They're dead.
They're all dead.

20:31.665 --> 20:34.363
Watch your--watch your step.
Okay.

20:34.407 --> 20:36.278
Oh, this is not good.

20:36.322 --> 20:44.286
- ♪

20:44.330 --> 20:49.683
- [heartbeat]

20:49.726 --> 20:51.554
- Sweetheart?

20:54.644 --> 20:55.906
Are you okay?

20:55.950 --> 20:57.604
- [shrieks]

20:57.647 --> 21:01.085
- [screaming]

21:01.129 --> 21:06.656
- [gunfire]

21:09.703 --> 21:12.009
- Come on, come on, come on!

21:12.053 --> 21:14.534
- [gunfire]

21:14.577 --> 21:16.797
- MAI: [shrieks]

21:21.976 --> 21:33.944
- ♪

21:36.425 --> 21:38.514
- OFFICER: Oh!
Stay put, Congressman.

21:38.558 --> 21:40.516
I'll take care of this.

21:40.560 --> 21:48.872
- ♪

21:48.916 --> 21:51.310
- Miss? You okay in there?

21:56.097 --> 21:57.272
- [gunshot]
- Whoa!

21:57.316 --> 21:59.143
Shit, damn it!

21:59.187 --> 22:02.625
- Do not come in here unless
you have my daughter's body!

22:02.669 --> 22:05.585
- Ma'am, come on now!
- It's all your fault!

22:05.628 --> 22:07.543
She just needed her medicine!

22:07.587 --> 22:10.851
- I cannot let that thing cross
the border, you know that.

22:10.894 --> 22:16.117
- That "thing" is my daughter
and she's an American citizen.

22:16.160 --> 22:19.250
- Excuse me, ma'am, but
I'm not sure if that fact

22:19.294 --> 22:22.732
has much relevance
at this exact moment.

22:22.776 --> 22:24.473
Miss?

22:24.517 --> 22:25.735
- [gunshot]
- Whoa!

22:25.779 --> 22:27.737
Doggone it!

22:27.781 --> 22:30.914
- EVAN: Officer!
I found something!

22:30.958 --> 22:34.527
- Fine.
Okay, ma'am. It's okay.

22:40.315 --> 22:44.101
Uh, uh, get it, get it, get it.

22:44.145 --> 22:46.060
The mother wants the body.

22:46.103 --> 22:48.149
I don't see any choice.

22:48.192 --> 22:50.151
That thing needs
to be destroyed.

22:52.371 --> 22:54.416
- MAI: [shrieks]

22:54.460 --> 22:56.375
- Where is that coming from?

22:56.418 --> 22:58.377
- [shrieks]

22:58.420 --> 23:00.379
- We got your goddamn body!

23:03.338 --> 23:06.080
- Oh, sweetheart! Thank god.

23:06.123 --> 23:14.567
- ♪

23:14.610 --> 23:16.307
- [grunts]
- [shrieks]

23:16.351 --> 23:19.354
- No, no, no!
It's not her fault!

23:19.398 --> 23:22.879
She just needed her medicine!

23:22.923 --> 23:24.925
And now it's too late.

23:24.968 --> 23:26.448
- [grunts]
- [shrieks]

23:26.492 --> 23:28.450
- [sobbing] No, no, no.

23:28.494 --> 23:31.584
No, please!
You're killing her!

23:31.627 --> 23:38.634
- ♪

23:38.678 --> 23:40.723
- I got it.

23:40.767 --> 23:44.423
I gotta put this little
one out of her misery.

23:44.466 --> 23:45.467
[grunts] I'm sorry.

23:45.511 --> 23:48.949
- MAI: [yells]

23:48.992 --> 23:51.342
- OFFICER: It's the only way.
I'm sorry, sweetheart.

23:51.386 --> 23:52.866
- [sobs]

23:52.909 --> 23:54.563
- OFFICER: [grunts]
- MAI: [shrieks]

23:54.607 --> 23:56.696
- [sobs]

24:01.788 --> 24:05.052
I'm sorry, Mai.

24:05.095 --> 24:08.359
I'm so sorry.

24:08.403 --> 24:13.582
- ♪

24:13.626 --> 24:15.802
- [grunts]
- [squish]

24:17.586 --> 24:20.546
- [pants]

24:22.461 --> 24:25.072
All quiet.

24:25.115 --> 24:27.596
Mission accomplished, I guess.

24:27.640 --> 24:29.163
- [clank]

24:30.643 --> 24:36.562
- [panting]

24:43.177 --> 24:46.920
- ♪

24:46.963 --> 24:49.575
- Oh, yeah.

24:49.618 --> 24:52.142
- Sorry about your wife, sir.

24:52.186 --> 24:53.535
- Yeah.

24:55.842 --> 24:58.497
I'm sure once the
adrenaline wears off,

24:58.540 --> 25:00.411
I'll feel something about that.

25:02.196 --> 25:03.763
Thank you, man.

25:03.806 --> 25:06.592
I'm sure my campaign can
squeeze a few extra ounces

25:06.635 --> 25:08.637
of political sympathy out of it.

25:08.681 --> 25:09.943
- Hmm.

25:13.686 --> 25:16.732
- [cries]

25:21.607 --> 25:25.219
- OFFICER: You know what?
There's a lesson here somewhere.

25:25.262 --> 25:28.396
- Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

25:28.439 --> 25:31.791
I mean, fucking
immigrants, right?

25:31.834 --> 25:36.099
- Oh, you racist piece of shit!
What the hell?

25:36.143 --> 25:39.450
Is that the first thing
that comes to your mind?

25:39.494 --> 25:43.150
- Oh, well, I mean, maybe
there's something about putting

25:43.193 --> 25:45.892
our political and ideological
differences aside

25:45.935 --> 25:48.982
to come together
to fight a common enemy.

25:49.025 --> 25:51.245
- I was just thinking...

25:51.288 --> 25:54.291
if this poor girl had proper
access to her medication,

25:54.335 --> 25:56.250
I mean, who knows, right?

25:58.208 --> 25:59.819
Weren't you just up in Canada

25:59.862 --> 26:02.648
trying to sell that exact
same message to your management?

26:02.691 --> 26:06.129
- EVAN: Comrade, I will do
whatever my PR firm tells me

26:06.173 --> 26:08.001
I need to do to get elected.

26:08.044 --> 26:10.438
I mean, shit, even if I do win,

26:10.481 --> 26:13.049
do you think there's one member
of Congress that's gonna vote to

26:13.093 --> 26:16.357
put a price cap
on prescription medication?

26:16.400 --> 26:17.619
I didn't run to fight battles

26:17.663 --> 26:19.447
neither side really wants
to win.

26:19.490 --> 26:24.321
- Dude, that's some grade A
fucking cynicism there, buddy.

26:24.365 --> 26:27.150
Why even run for office?

26:27.194 --> 26:31.328
- I mean, beats working
like a peasant, right?

26:32.939 --> 26:36.072
Plus, ironically, the job

26:36.116 --> 26:37.683
actually comes with
some pretty damn good

26:37.726 --> 26:39.554
government-provided
health insurance.

26:44.298 --> 26:46.126
- What's your co-pay?

26:46.169 --> 26:47.562
- [snickers]

26:47.606 --> 26:50.478
- BOTH: [laughing]

26:52.219 --> 27:04.187
- ♪

27:34.261 --> 27:41.660
♪

27:42.835 --> 27:54.803
- ♪

28:00.461 --> 28:05.031
- [clanking]

28:08.425 --> 28:18.697
- ♪

28:45.288 --> 28:52.687
♪

28:52.731 --> 28:55.211
- [evil cackling]

29:00.390 --> 29:08.572
- ♪

29:08.616 --> 29:11.488
- [horn blaring]

29:13.055 --> 29:25.024
- ♪

29:32.248 --> 29:33.510
- MALE REPORTER: Because
of the obvious threat

29:33.554 --> 29:35.121
to untold numbers of citizens,

29:35.164 --> 29:37.645
and because of the crisis
which is even now developing,

29:37.688 --> 29:41.040
this radio station will remain
on the air day and night.

29:41.083 --> 29:43.738
This station and hundreds of
other radio and TV stations

29:43.782 --> 29:45.348
throughout this part of
the country

29:45.392 --> 29:46.915
are pooling their
resources through

29:46.959 --> 29:49.222
an emergency network
hookup to keep you informed

29:49.265 --> 29:51.398
of all developments.

29:51.441 --> 29:53.226
- [static]

29:53.269 --> 29:56.403
- [indistinct chatter]

29:56.446 --> 30:00.407
- [cars pulling up]
- [car doors shutting]

30:03.976 --> 30:05.412
- REPORTER: --murder
being committed by

30:05.455 --> 30:07.806
a virtual army of
unidentified assassins.

30:07.849 --> 30:09.155
It seems to be a sudden,

30:09.198 --> 30:12.071
general explosion of
mass homicide.

30:12.114 --> 30:13.855
When this emergency
first began,

30:13.899 --> 30:15.770
radio and television
was advising people

30:15.814 --> 30:19.600
to stay inside
behind locked doors for safety.

30:19.643 --> 30:22.995
Well, that situation
has now changed.

30:23.038 --> 30:24.866
- [doorbell rings]

30:27.564 --> 30:29.175
- Howdy, boys.

30:29.218 --> 30:32.047
- [crickets chirping]

30:33.179 --> 30:35.050
- Uh, I have...

30:35.094 --> 30:36.530
- Joe?

30:38.314 --> 30:41.013
- [crickets chirping]

30:47.671 --> 30:50.239
- We're headed out
to Ridgeway House, Evan.

30:50.283 --> 30:51.937
We're going for Cliven.

30:54.983 --> 30:56.463
- Boys, uh, I know you all have

30:56.506 --> 31:00.032
good reasons to be angry,
but, um...

31:00.075 --> 31:02.251
it's probably best
we stay inside.

31:02.295 --> 31:03.905
Wait for the
National Guard to get here.

31:03.949 --> 31:05.907
- Radio says military ain't
gettin' here 'til Tuesday

31:05.951 --> 31:07.474
at the earliest.

31:07.517 --> 31:09.258
- With all the chaos
going on around here,

31:09.302 --> 31:12.609
no one's ever gonna
know what happened to him.

31:12.653 --> 31:14.742
- You know I can't sanction
something like this.

31:14.785 --> 31:17.005
- We're not asking
permission, Chief.

31:19.399 --> 31:21.314
We want you to join us.

31:21.357 --> 31:23.838
- [helicopter whirring overhead]

31:23.882 --> 31:25.448
- No.

31:26.493 --> 31:28.451
I'm not joining ya 'cuz

31:28.495 --> 31:31.367
y'all ain't doing
nothing but going home.

31:31.411 --> 31:33.935
- Evan, how many times have
you put that boy behind bars?

31:33.979 --> 31:35.806
- As many as it takes.

31:35.850 --> 31:38.940
- It not gonna stick as long
as his daddy runs the show.

31:38.984 --> 31:41.421
- Yeah, he can do
whatever he wants.

31:41.464 --> 31:44.467
Just ask my brother's family.

31:44.511 --> 31:46.252
- My sister.

31:46.295 --> 31:48.297
- Or worse.

31:48.341 --> 31:50.299
What he done to my daughter.

31:50.343 --> 31:55.914
- [crickets chirping]
- [light traffic]

31:55.957 --> 31:57.350
- I'm sorry, Joe,
there's no evidence--

31:57.393 --> 31:58.699
- Horseshit!

32:00.483 --> 32:01.963
- Loopholes.

32:06.837 --> 32:10.319
- I'm not gonna say it again.

32:10.363 --> 32:15.150
We don't do vigilante
justice in this town.

32:15.194 --> 32:19.067
That goes for all of you.

32:19.111 --> 32:20.155
Now get.

32:20.199 --> 32:22.766
- Well...

32:22.810 --> 32:25.944
if I see him on my
way home tonight...

32:25.987 --> 32:28.076
who knows?

32:28.120 --> 32:31.471
- Carl, you're better than this.
- Used to be.

32:31.514 --> 32:33.299
Maybe not no more.

32:36.041 --> 32:38.957
- Carl. I'm riding with you.

32:41.611 --> 32:43.439
You keep taking
the high road, Chief!

32:43.483 --> 32:45.398
We'll take the other way.

32:45.441 --> 32:46.921
- You boys do anything tonight

32:46.965 --> 32:48.792
and tomorrow it'll be the law
that gets ya!

32:48.836 --> 32:50.272
- The law?

32:50.316 --> 32:53.406
[chuckles] Ain't no
law no more, Chief.

32:53.449 --> 32:55.886
Don't you get it?

32:55.930 --> 32:58.324
- [truck door shuts]
- [truck starts]

33:09.509 --> 33:11.554
- Aw, shit!

33:11.598 --> 33:13.034
I'mma try to
beat them out there.

33:13.078 --> 33:14.949
You go find Tommy and
take a ride through town,

33:14.993 --> 33:16.864
see if Cliven's hanging around!

33:23.305 --> 33:26.700
- [car starts]

33:26.743 --> 33:38.712
- ♪

33:44.413 --> 33:46.372
- Fuckin' last thing I wanna
be doing tonight, Cliven,

33:46.415 --> 33:48.026
is saving your dumb ass.

33:48.069 --> 33:49.549
- REPORTER ON RADIO: Repeating
this latest bulletin

33:49.592 --> 33:51.899
just received moments ago
from Cumberland, Maryland.

33:51.942 --> 33:55.250
Civil Defense authorities have
told newsmen that murder victims

33:55.294 --> 33:57.774
show evidence of having
been partially devoured

33:57.818 --> 34:00.038
by their murderers.

34:00.081 --> 34:01.517
- POLICE RADIO: Chief?
- REPORTER: Medical examination

34:01.561 --> 34:03.606
of victims' bodies
shows conclusively--

34:03.650 --> 34:05.043
- POLICE RADIO: Tommy
says he saw Cliven's GTO

34:05.086 --> 34:07.262
when he was on patrol
about 10 minutes ago

34:07.306 --> 34:10.091
parked outside
the old wire factory.

34:10.135 --> 34:11.919
- Shit!

34:11.962 --> 34:13.921
- [tires screeching]

34:13.964 --> 34:17.925
- [insects chirping, buzzing]

34:33.941 --> 34:37.031
- The hell you doin' all
the way out here, Cliven?

34:37.075 --> 34:48.608
- ♪

34:57.399 --> 35:03.144
♪

35:03.188 --> 35:06.713
- [gunshot]
- [thudding]

35:14.460 --> 35:18.333
- [creaking]

35:21.815 --> 35:23.773
- CHIEF: Oh.

35:23.817 --> 35:25.645
My god...

35:25.688 --> 35:34.828
- ♪

35:34.871 --> 35:39.180
- [coughs]

35:39.224 --> 35:43.750
- [creaking]

35:43.793 --> 35:52.802
- ♪

36:08.818 --> 36:14.172
♪

36:14.215 --> 36:15.999
- [groans]

36:19.177 --> 36:21.091
Oh, Edda.

36:27.924 --> 36:31.928
- [creak]
- [moaning]

36:31.972 --> 36:33.495
- This is Police Chief Foster.

36:33.539 --> 36:34.801
Whoever that is better
step into the light now

36:34.844 --> 36:37.543
and keep your hands where
I can see 'em!

36:37.586 --> 36:39.327
- [ding]
- Oof!

36:39.371 --> 36:40.720
- Cliven!

36:43.679 --> 36:45.464
- Well, well.

36:45.507 --> 36:47.335
If it ain't my
daddy's pet po-lice.

36:47.379 --> 36:49.685
What you doin' all the
way out here, Chief?

36:49.729 --> 36:51.861
- Lookin' for ya.
Whole town's lookin' for ya.

36:51.905 --> 36:53.123
A group of Carl Fenston's boys

36:53.167 --> 36:55.213
wanna put you in the grave
tonight.

36:55.256 --> 36:56.562
Joe Donovan, too.

36:56.605 --> 36:59.434
- Oh, not that again.

36:59.478 --> 37:01.001
- CHIEF: Care to explain this?

37:01.044 --> 37:06.093
- ♪

37:06.136 --> 37:07.573
- Crazy old bat.
I thought she was

37:07.616 --> 37:09.966
some kind of squatter or
somethin' comin' after me.

37:10.010 --> 37:11.490
Or one of them things
on the news, you know?

37:11.533 --> 37:13.056
You've seen them things--
- From the looks of it,

37:13.100 --> 37:14.928
I think you'd better
come up with a better story.

37:14.971 --> 37:16.059
- [scoffs]

37:20.586 --> 37:23.502
You think I did this,
chewed on her arm?

37:23.545 --> 37:25.199
Ain't you seen the news?

37:25.243 --> 37:26.548
It's open season on them thing--

37:26.592 --> 37:29.334
- That's in the cities.

37:29.377 --> 37:31.074
Not here.

37:31.118 --> 37:33.294
Not in my town.

37:33.338 --> 37:37.298
- [laughs]

37:37.342 --> 37:39.605
Your town?
This ain't your town.

37:39.648 --> 37:41.215
This is my daddy's town.

37:41.259 --> 37:43.435
Last I checked, a mayor's
more important than a,

37:43.478 --> 37:47.830
uh--a guard dog.

37:47.874 --> 37:51.921
- Cliven, to be clear,

37:51.965 --> 37:53.532
I've got half a mind
to leave you be and

37:53.575 --> 37:55.316
let these boys track you--
- Hey, hey, look.

37:55.360 --> 37:58.537
I ain't been convicted of--
- Let me finish.

37:58.580 --> 37:59.886
- Okay.

37:59.929 --> 38:03.324
- All you done, it'd
serve you right.

38:03.368 --> 38:05.457
But that ain't my way.

38:05.500 --> 38:07.241
As soon as this town
stops following the rules,

38:07.285 --> 38:09.417
won't be a town left to save,
so you're comin' with me.

38:11.593 --> 38:13.291
- Oh.

38:13.334 --> 38:15.075
I feel so safe.

38:15.118 --> 38:16.685
[mocking] Big boy's
gonna protect me--

38:16.729 --> 38:21.124
- Put the rifle down and
your hands on the wall!

38:21.168 --> 38:22.648
- Easy, Chief.

38:29.524 --> 38:31.396
- Cliven, you know damn
well how to be arrested.

38:31.439 --> 38:33.354
- [growling]

38:33.398 --> 38:38.141
- ♪

38:38.185 --> 38:40.709
- [growling]

38:43.669 --> 38:45.627
- Look at that.

38:45.671 --> 38:49.762
Whole town--
- Shut up!

38:49.805 --> 38:52.330
- CLIVEN: I'm feeling
like a celebrity.

38:52.373 --> 38:55.768
Everybody's lookin'
for ol' Cliven.

38:55.811 --> 38:58.292
- I got a bad
feeling about this.

38:58.336 --> 39:03.471
- ♪

39:03.515 --> 39:05.560
- Cliven!

39:05.604 --> 39:13.742
- ♪

39:13.786 --> 39:16.354
- CLIVEN: Well, it looks like
I'm the one saving you from

39:16.397 --> 39:18.573
the mob tonight, Chief.

39:18.617 --> 39:22.011
A little thank
you would be nice.

39:22.055 --> 39:23.883
[clears throat]

39:27.626 --> 39:31.412
That's the problem
with you people.

39:31.456 --> 39:33.893
No gratitude, no nothin'.

39:37.113 --> 39:39.246
That's to tie up my dogs.

39:39.289 --> 39:41.901
I bring 'em out
here for...training.

39:41.944 --> 39:43.642
Rowdy bitches, those ones.

39:43.685 --> 39:45.426
Rowdy bitches!

39:45.470 --> 39:51.301
- ♪

39:51.345 --> 39:53.695
- Sometimes you just
gotta break 'em down.

39:53.739 --> 39:57.220
Let 'em know what's what.

39:57.264 --> 40:01.050
You know what I mean?

40:01.094 --> 40:02.443
- [grunts]
- Oh, fuck!

40:02.487 --> 40:04.358
What the fuck, man?

40:04.402 --> 40:06.969
- Cliven Ridgeway,
you're under arrest.

40:07.013 --> 40:09.798
- What for? The fuck for?
That old lady over there?

40:09.842 --> 40:11.670
I told you, she came at me!

40:11.713 --> 40:13.541
You heard the news.
It's open season on them things!

40:13.585 --> 40:15.282
Ow!

40:15.325 --> 40:18.067
- Last time I saw Edda, she
was alive as you and me.

40:18.111 --> 40:19.721
Until I know different,
that means it's homicide,

40:19.765 --> 40:22.463
and that puts you behind bars.

40:24.291 --> 40:26.554
- Okay. Okay.

40:26.598 --> 40:29.427
Ow, ow! Ow, ow!

40:33.735 --> 40:35.128
[sniffs]

40:36.651 --> 40:38.697
So that's what this is, huh?

40:38.740 --> 40:42.004
Railroad job.

40:42.048 --> 40:44.572
And now you're driving me to
jail in a car my family bought

40:44.616 --> 40:46.313
the department.

40:46.356 --> 40:48.184
- I thanked your folks at
the ribbon-cutting ceremony.

40:48.228 --> 40:50.099
That don't excuse you of murder.

40:52.537 --> 40:54.669
- Only it's not Edda Winterson's
murder you're arresting me for,

40:54.713 --> 40:56.497
is it?

41:00.501 --> 41:03.199
- Carl Fenston, this is
Police Chief Foster.

41:03.243 --> 41:04.810
Carl, you got your ears on?

41:04.853 --> 41:06.551
- CARL: 10-2, is
that you, Chief?

41:06.594 --> 41:08.030
- 10-12.

41:08.074 --> 41:10.337
I'm on a backstroke here.

41:10.380 --> 41:11.904
And I got Cliven
Ridgeway with me.

41:11.947 --> 41:13.732
- The hell you
talkin' to him for?

41:13.775 --> 41:15.255
- Shut up.
- CARL: Well, what do you know?

41:15.298 --> 41:17.953
Guess who decided
to join the party.

41:17.997 --> 41:20.390
- What's that supposed
to mean, party?

41:20.434 --> 41:22.523
- I'm en route back
to the station.

41:22.567 --> 41:25.439
I want you and Jeremy to
meet me there, got it?

41:25.483 --> 41:27.876
- CARL: Yes, sir!

41:27.920 --> 41:31.097
Glad to see you had a
change of heart, Chief.

41:31.140 --> 41:33.882
- Hey! I thought you were
protecting me from them.

41:33.926 --> 41:34.840
Now you're calling them in?

41:34.883 --> 41:37.756
[scoffs, laughs]

41:37.799 --> 41:39.932
I know my fuckin' rights
here, Chief.

41:39.975 --> 41:45.241
- ♪

41:45.285 --> 41:47.809
- Okay, look, Foster.

41:47.853 --> 41:50.856
There's only two ways
this is gonna go.

41:50.899 --> 41:52.901
Either the courthouse opens
tomorrow and the judge hands me

41:52.945 --> 41:55.251
a get out of jail free card,

41:55.295 --> 41:58.864
or the courts never open again
and you let me out

41:58.907 --> 42:01.344
on account of there ain't
no fucking courts anymore!

42:04.086 --> 42:06.088
They! Ain't! Never!

42:06.132 --> 42:10.397
Gonna! Put! Me! In! Jail!

42:15.184 --> 42:16.621
[spits]

42:18.144 --> 42:20.059
[mocking]
I'm Chief Foster!

42:20.102 --> 42:22.322
I think I'm big and bad!

42:22.365 --> 42:25.238
I got a badge and a gun.
I'm the law!

42:26.805 --> 42:28.807
- [crickets chirping]

42:28.850 --> 42:33.420
- ♪

42:33.463 --> 42:35.553
- CLIVEN: Fuckin' shit!

42:37.424 --> 42:39.208
What is this?

42:39.252 --> 42:40.819
Hey, what is it?

42:40.862 --> 42:42.385
Hey!

42:42.429 --> 42:44.997
Fuck are you doing?

42:45.040 --> 42:46.346
- Evening, Chief.

42:46.389 --> 42:48.522
- Good evening, Chief.
- Hi, boys.

42:48.566 --> 42:50.045
- What you got?

42:50.089 --> 42:53.875
- [sighs] Got me an idea.

42:53.919 --> 42:56.051
- CARL: What's your idea?

42:56.095 --> 42:57.487
- It's a little unsavory, but--

42:57.531 --> 42:58.967
- What the fuck is he--

42:59.011 --> 43:00.969
- CHIEF: I want your
boys to pick up Sue.

43:02.710 --> 43:04.930
Don't have to if
it's asking too much.

43:04.973 --> 43:07.672
- Never wanted to do
something more in my life.

43:07.715 --> 43:09.587
- [pants]

43:09.630 --> 43:11.066
- CHIEF: Shouldn't
take you that long.

43:11.110 --> 43:12.502
- I'll tell the others.

43:16.332 --> 43:17.986
- That son of a bitch.

43:18.030 --> 43:19.597
That son of a bitch.

43:19.640 --> 43:25.341
- ♪

43:25.385 --> 43:26.691
- Oh god.

43:28.649 --> 43:30.477
Fuck! Fuck!

43:30.520 --> 43:32.827
- [truck starts]

43:39.486 --> 43:42.184
- Hey! You better hope that
Tastee Freeze is hiring,

43:42.228 --> 43:43.838
you pencil-neck son of a bitch!

43:43.882 --> 43:46.624
'Cuz you're gonna be out
on your freakin' ass! Hah!

43:46.667 --> 43:49.583
- Get up! Get up! Get up!

43:49.627 --> 43:52.107
- Okay, okay, you can't
treat me like this, Foster.

43:52.151 --> 43:53.805
I'm the mayor's son.

43:53.848 --> 43:55.720
The mayor's son!

43:55.763 --> 43:57.112
- REPORTER:
--wave of murder which is

43:57.156 --> 43:58.723
sweeping the eastern third
of the nation

43:58.766 --> 44:01.551
is being committed
by creatures who feast upon

44:01.595 --> 44:04.250
the flesh of their victims.

44:04.293 --> 44:06.382
- I'm not arresting you for
something you didn't do, Cliven.

44:06.426 --> 44:08.341
But not being convicted
of a crime ain't the same

44:08.384 --> 44:10.038
as not having committed it.

44:10.082 --> 44:11.866
That's a lesson I don't
think you've learned.

44:11.910 --> 44:14.216
- REPORTER: However,
reports persisted.

44:14.260 --> 44:17.567
Medical examinations of some of
the victims bore out the fact

44:17.611 --> 44:19.874
that they had been
partially devoured.

44:23.835 --> 44:27.621
- [clanking]

44:27.665 --> 44:30.319
- At least buy me a
drink first, sweetheart.

44:30.363 --> 44:33.148
- Sweetheart, hm.

44:33.192 --> 44:36.848
Is that what you called Joe
Donovan's daughter, Cliven?

44:36.891 --> 44:42.070
- ♪

44:42.114 --> 44:44.594
- Oh, so that's
what this is about.

44:44.638 --> 44:48.598
I fucking told you I had nothing
to do with that little girl.

44:48.642 --> 44:51.036
I got eyewitnesses
to back up my alibi.

44:51.079 --> 44:55.518
You got nothin'.
No evidence, nothing!

44:55.562 --> 44:59.044
- Yup. You got me there.

44:59.087 --> 45:02.351
Normally we'd have all the
evidence we need, but, uh,

45:02.395 --> 45:05.180
the only forensic tech we
got access to suddenly decided

45:05.224 --> 45:09.097
to go on a European vacation,
of all things.

45:09.141 --> 45:11.970
First class tickets,
Four Seasons Hotel.

45:12.013 --> 45:14.712
Helluva trip for
someone on his wages.

45:14.755 --> 45:17.018
- That sounds lovely.

45:17.062 --> 45:18.280
I can't control
when someone decides

45:18.324 --> 45:19.847
to take a fuckin' vacation.

45:19.891 --> 45:23.329
- Nah, you can't.

45:23.372 --> 45:25.505
I expect that was your daddy.

45:28.247 --> 45:30.684
- Hey!

45:30.728 --> 45:32.251
You gonna let me
out of these cuffs?

45:32.294 --> 45:33.774
- Nah, I don't think
I will tonight.

45:37.473 --> 45:39.171
- You can't leave
me in here, Chief!

45:39.214 --> 45:40.694
Not with what's
going on out there.

45:40.738 --> 45:42.087
It's not safe.

45:42.130 --> 45:43.915
It ain't right,
that's for goddamn sure!

45:43.958 --> 45:45.481
- CHIEF:
Probably the safest place

45:45.525 --> 45:46.961
you can be right now, Cliven.

45:47.005 --> 45:48.876
For a little while, anyway.

45:48.920 --> 45:50.399
I mean, according to you,

45:50.443 --> 45:52.793
the judge'll have you out
come morning.

45:52.837 --> 45:55.535
So nothin' to
worry about, right?

45:55.578 --> 45:57.929
- [footsteps]

46:00.322 --> 46:03.543
- [door slams]
- Son of a bitch!

46:03.586 --> 46:05.719
- This is the latest disclosure,
in a report from

46:05.763 --> 46:08.113
National Civil Defense
Headquarters in Washington.

46:09.636 --> 46:12.639
It has been established that
persons who have recently died

46:12.682 --> 46:16.861
have been returning to life
and committing acts of murder.

46:16.904 --> 46:18.601
- [doorbell rings]

46:18.645 --> 46:20.081
- REPORTER: A widespread
investigation of reports from

46:20.125 --> 46:22.997
funeral homes, morgues,
and hospitals has concluded

46:23.041 --> 46:26.305
that the unburied dead
are coming back to life

46:26.348 --> 46:29.438
and seeking human victims.

46:29.482 --> 46:32.050
It's hard for us here to believe
what we're reporting to you,

46:32.093 --> 46:33.921
but it does seem to be a fact.

46:33.965 --> 46:35.618
- ♪

46:35.662 --> 46:37.620
- [banging]

46:41.146 --> 46:42.800
- What?

46:43.975 --> 46:46.629
[groans]

46:48.718 --> 46:50.851
Cassius-fucken-Clay.

46:50.895 --> 47:02.863
- ♪

47:02.907 --> 47:04.430
- The hell are you
all doing here?

47:04.473 --> 47:08.651
- They're, um,
interested parties.

47:08.695 --> 47:10.262
- Interested?

47:12.264 --> 47:13.831
Oh, okay.

47:15.528 --> 47:18.923
I see what we got here.
You're rounding up everyone

47:18.966 --> 47:22.535
who ever held a grudge against
old Cliven Ridgeway, huh?

47:22.578 --> 47:24.493
There's gonna be
a public execution.

47:27.496 --> 47:30.760
I thought you were a man
of the law, Foster, but no.

47:30.804 --> 47:33.285
You're gonna put a bullet in
me while these assholes watch.

47:33.328 --> 47:34.895
- Why would I do that?

47:34.939 --> 47:36.679
- 'Cuz you believe all the
shit they talk about me.

47:36.723 --> 47:40.683
What--what, uh, Carl says I
did to his brother's silo.

47:40.727 --> 47:43.817
What Jeremy said I did to
his sister on prom night.

47:43.861 --> 47:45.253
Chub, I don't even
know what I did to you.

47:45.297 --> 47:48.343
I thought we were friends.

47:48.387 --> 47:51.825
What Joe Donovan said
I did to his daughter.

47:51.869 --> 47:55.481
What he thinks I
did to his daughter.

47:55.524 --> 47:59.224
- You got off on
all those, Cliven.

47:59.267 --> 48:02.792
- Yeah. But we sure
as hell ain't here

48:02.836 --> 48:06.709
because of all that
at the wire factory.

48:06.753 --> 48:10.931
- You got one chance to
say something decent here.

48:10.975 --> 48:13.803
So I'm gonna ask you.

48:13.847 --> 48:16.458
You got something you
wanna confess to us?

48:16.502 --> 48:27.208
- ♪

48:37.784 --> 48:39.612
- Fuck you.

48:39.655 --> 48:42.397
Fuck you all!

48:42.441 --> 48:44.008
[spits]

48:48.142 --> 48:51.319
- [shrieking, shouting]
- [gunfire]

48:51.363 --> 48:54.757
- MAN: Hold it, damn it!
- The hell's that, Foster?

48:54.801 --> 48:59.849
- So...the thing of it is...

48:59.893 --> 49:02.940
because that forensic
tech was in Europe,

49:02.983 --> 49:05.681
we had to send Sue Donovan's
body to Somerset County for

49:05.725 --> 49:08.380
the autopsy, or at least
we were supposed to.

49:08.423 --> 49:12.906
They're so backed up on
cases, as you can imagine.

49:12.950 --> 49:16.388
She's still sitting
in the morgue.

49:16.431 --> 49:18.520
You see where I'm getting at?

49:18.564 --> 49:20.435
- I got no idea of why
you're rapping on about

49:20.479 --> 49:21.828
some dead girl's autopsy.

49:21.871 --> 49:25.484
- Not some dead girl.

49:25.527 --> 49:27.965
Her name was Sue, Cliven.

49:28.008 --> 49:30.054
Sue Donovan.

49:30.097 --> 49:32.012
- Yeah! Yeah, I know!

49:32.056 --> 49:34.493
And you and her crazy-ass father
had the whole goddamn town

49:34.536 --> 49:35.885
believing I did
something to her.

49:35.929 --> 49:37.583
Some fucking sheep you are!

49:37.626 --> 49:40.890
- Point is...if they'd
performed the autopsy

49:40.934 --> 49:42.805
during the
normal course of events,

49:42.849 --> 49:46.679
they would've taken
her brain out to weigh it.

49:46.722 --> 49:50.639
But in this case, they
just did the measurements,

49:50.683 --> 49:53.033
put it in a jar.

49:53.077 --> 49:56.123
- [pants] You
mean--you mean she--

49:56.167 --> 49:57.733
- [banging at door]

49:59.561 --> 50:02.608
- ♪

50:02.651 --> 50:06.394
- [pants]

50:09.136 --> 50:11.486
What is that, Foster?

50:11.530 --> 50:13.140
- You know what it is.

50:17.971 --> 50:19.451
- No!

50:21.540 --> 50:22.976
No. What are you doing?

50:23.020 --> 50:24.543
- Chief.
- Carl.

50:24.586 --> 50:26.110
- Carl, no!

50:26.153 --> 50:28.808
Jeremy, no, don't bring
that thing in here!

50:28.851 --> 50:31.071
Come on! Come on!

50:34.379 --> 50:36.816
Chief, no! Chief, no!

50:36.859 --> 50:37.991
Chief!

50:38.035 --> 50:39.906
- [growling]

50:39.949 --> 50:42.474
- [gasps] Aah!

50:42.517 --> 50:44.780
Come on!

50:44.824 --> 50:46.347
- [hissing]

50:46.391 --> 50:49.655
- Can I know, Chief,
what changed your mind?

50:49.698 --> 50:52.353
- Foster! Jeremy!
Come--Come on!

50:52.397 --> 50:53.789
- You know, when these things
started coming back

50:53.833 --> 50:56.792
from the dead, I was...

50:56.836 --> 51:00.318
I thought it was the end times.
I was right and truly scared.

51:00.361 --> 51:01.449
- [growling]

51:01.493 --> 51:03.712
- Come on! [unintelligible]

51:03.756 --> 51:08.369
- Then I saw something
tonight, something...worse.

51:08.413 --> 51:13.766
- CLIVEN: [gasps]

51:13.809 --> 51:18.423
- [raspy breathing]

51:18.466 --> 51:21.556
- What was it?
What did you see?

51:21.600 --> 51:25.734
- ♪

51:25.778 --> 51:27.606
- CHIEF: This.

51:32.132 --> 51:35.135
- [gasps]

51:35.179 --> 51:47.104
- ♪

51:58.550 --> 52:01.248
- CLIVEN: [pants, whimpers]

52:01.292 --> 52:03.207
- [growls]

52:03.250 --> 52:06.427
- [gasps]

52:06.471 --> 52:08.603
- [hisses]

52:08.647 --> 52:10.170
- CLIVEN: Oh no. No.

52:10.214 --> 52:12.129
No, no, no, no. No.

52:12.172 --> 52:15.262
[pants] No.

52:15.306 --> 52:17.221
[grunts]

52:20.789 --> 52:23.183
Oh, god, no. No.

52:23.227 --> 52:25.229
- [growls]

52:25.272 --> 52:28.667
Aah! Aah! Aah!

52:28.710 --> 52:31.017
[screams]
- [growls, hisses]

52:31.060 --> 52:33.411
- CLIVEN: Foster! No!
[sobs] No!

52:33.454 --> 52:35.456
Aah! Aah!

52:35.500 --> 52:38.329
[screams]

52:38.372 --> 52:42.811
Oh god! Oh god!

52:42.855 --> 52:46.554
Aah! Aah! Aah!

52:46.598 --> 52:49.992
[pants]

52:50.036 --> 52:51.907
Oh god, oh god.

52:51.951 --> 52:53.866
[screams]

52:53.909 --> 52:56.608
Oh my god!

52:56.651 --> 52:59.088
[screams]

52:59.132 --> 53:01.613
- You know, if this
is the end times...

53:01.656 --> 53:03.571
maybe we deserve it.

53:09.229 --> 53:12.014
You heard what the news said.
There's no more rules.

53:12.058 --> 53:13.625
Let's go find his daddy.

53:13.668 --> 53:15.496
- Yeah, okay!

53:15.540 --> 53:17.368
- Chief, if I were surrounded
by six or eight of these things,

53:17.411 --> 53:18.891
would I stand a
chance with them?

53:18.934 --> 53:20.327
- Well, there's no problem.

53:20.371 --> 53:21.807
If you have a gun,
shoot 'em in the head.

53:21.850 --> 53:23.330
That's a sure way to kill 'em.

53:23.374 --> 53:25.114
If you don't, get yourself
a club or a torch.

53:25.158 --> 53:27.334
Beat 'em or burn 'em.
They go up pretty easy.

53:27.378 --> 53:29.336
- Well, Chief McClellan, how
long do you think it will

53:29.380 --> 53:31.947
take you until you get
the situation under control?

53:31.991 --> 53:33.471
- Well, that's
pretty hard to say.

53:33.514 --> 53:35.124
We don't know how
many of 'em there are.

53:35.168 --> 53:37.953
We know when we find
'em, we can kill 'em.

53:37.997 --> 53:39.694
- Are they slow-moving, Chief?

53:39.738 --> 53:43.220
- Yeah, they're dead.
They're...all messed up.

53:43.263 --> 53:50.618
- ♪

53:54.579 --> 53:56.450
- [thunder crashes]

53:56.494 --> 54:02.326
- ["CreepShow" theme music
plays]

54:17.558 --> 54:25.740
♪

54:25.784 --> 54:31.659
- [ghostly choir]

54:41.452 --> 54:47.240
- ♪♪
